    Our Projects

    Honeycomb Walks

    Collaborating with Big Team Challenge, and in support of Health in Mind, we, along with over 70 of our hive, walked the combined distance from Edinburgh to Singapore. As well as raising awareness around Health in Mind and mental health, we also managed to raise money for them at our fun run, where we launched the project, and at our school’s mini marathon, where over 900 students all ran a mile.

    Honeycomb Baking

    A big part of any fundraising effort is bound to be bake sales, and thanks to the amazing support of our Honeycomb Baking team, that was a possibility for us. As well as running several successful bake sales in our school and at events, we also collaborated with BlackRock, heading out to their Edinburgh office to run a doughnut sale thanks to Krispy Kreme’s charity dozen scheme.

    Honeycomb Green

    Since the start of the project, environmental sustainability has been a key focus for us, and it all falls under the banner of our Honeycomb Green sub-brand. On top of the work we already do, such as our commitment to using recycled materials and public transport at any possible opportunity, we’ve also worked with The Green Team, removing invasive rhododendron bushes from local woodlands.

    Honeycomb Space

    Our most ambitious project to date, Honeycomb Space encapsulates us partnering with Sent Into Space to, quite literally, send our car into space. This will allow us to get visuals that are out-of-this-world (both metaphorically and physically), and will give us an edge in our marketing and digital media that no other teams will be able to compete with.

    Honeycomb Primary

    One of the most important things to us being able to give back to our community, and that’s what Honeycomb Primary is about for us. We want to inspire a future generation of engineers the same way we were inspired when we were their age, and so, we’re going into primary schools local to us to teach them about F1, and to show them the opportunities open to them once they get to high school.

    Honeycomb Legacy

    When we started Honeycomb Racing, we weren’t sure what we were doing, and we were given little guidance from anyone on what to do. So, we want to create an environment for success at Gillespie’s that many schools already have, and leave behind resources and teaching that can inspire future teams to excel beyond what we have ever managed to do. Honeycomb Legacy isn’t just for now, it’s forever.
